#compdef gqlgen
# ============================================================================
# gqlgen - schema-first GraphQL server
#          generator for Go
#          (Go, MIT)
#
# Author : Patrik Adler + 99designs
#           engineering team + open-source
#           contributors (currently
#           maintained by Lucas Lorentz
#           and others after the 99designs
#           team's stewardship)
# Upstream: https://github.com/99designs/gqlgen
# Website: https://gqlgen.com
#
# `gqlgen` is THE canonical Go GraphQL
# server library + code generator. Unlike
# code-first GraphQL libraries (where you
# define Go types + use macros/struct tags
# to derive the schema), gqlgen is
# *schema-first*: you write a .graphql
# schema file + run `gqlgen generate` to
# produce strongly-typed Go resolver
# interfaces + boilerplate. Then you
# implement the resolver interfaces with
# your business logic.
#
# This schema-first approach provides:
#   - **Single source of truth** (the
#     .graphql schema file)
#   - **Type safety guarantees**
#     (generated Go code reflects the
#     schema exactly)
#   - **No runtime reflection** (all
#     resolver dispatch is compile-time
#     typed)
#   - **IDE-friendly** (generated Go
#     interfaces enable autocomplete +
#     refactoring)
#
# Architecture:
#   1. **Schema-first** (.graphql file is
#      the source of truth)
#   2. **Code generation** (gqlgen.yml
#      config + .graphql schema → Go
#      resolver interfaces + DTO types
#      + middleware wiring)
#   3. **Per-resolver implementation**
#     (user implements one Go method
#     per GraphQL field)
#   4. **HTTP server agnostic**
#     (works with net/http + chi + gin
#     + echo + any Go HTTP framework)
#   5. **Subscription support** (WebSocket
#     + Server-Sent Events transports)
#
# Distinguishing features vs alternatives
# (graphql-go + thunder + 0xfaded/jsonpath):
#   - **Schema-first** (most other Go
#     GraphQL libraries are code-first
#     using runtime reflection; gqlgen
#     is the canonical schema-first
#     library)
#   - **Strongly-typed resolvers**
#     (every resolver function has
#     concrete Go types - no
#     interface{} or map[string]
#     interface{} boilerplate)
#   - **Federation support** (Apollo
#     Federation v1 + v2 with @key +
#     @requires + @provides directives)
#   - **DataLoader integration**
#     (vektah/dataloaden codegen for
#     N+1 query prevention)
#   - **Plugin system** (codegen plugins
#     for customizing generated
#     output)
#   - **10,700+ stars on github.com/
#     99designs/gqlgen** (THE most-
#     starred Go GraphQL library by
#     a wide margin)
#
# Use cases:
#   - **Production GraphQL Go servers**
#     (used by 99designs, Shopify
#     internal services, many Go
#     microservice architectures)
#   - **Apollo Federation subgraph
#     implementations** (Go subgraphs
#     unified into a supergraph by an
#     Apollo Router or Hive Router)
#   - **Migrating REST → GraphQL Go
#     services** (the gqlgen
#     code-generation workflow makes
#     this transition manageable)
#   - **GraphQL-first API design**
#     (teams using schema-first design
#     across multiple language
#     ecosystems can use the same
#     .graphql files)
#
# Usage:
#   gqlgen [global flags] <command>
#         [command flags]
#
# Global flags (urfave/cli):
#       --config <file>            - gqlgen
#                                     config
#                                     file
#                                     (default:
#                                     ./
#                                     gqlgen
#                                     .yml or
#                                     ./
#                                     gqlgen
#                                     .yaml)
#       --verbose                  - verbose
#                                     output
#                                     (enable
#                                     debug
#                                     log
#                                     output)
#   -h, --help                     - show
#                                     help
#       --version                  - show
#                                     version
#
# Subcommands:
#   init                           - initialize
#                                     gqlgen
#                                     config
#                                     +
#                                     generate
#                                     models
#                                     +
#                                     resolvers
#                                     for a
#                                     new
#                                     project
#   generate                       - generate
#                                     Go code
#                                     from
#                                     the
#                                     GraphQL
#                                     schema
#                                     (default
#                                     command
#                                     when
#                                     gqlgen
#                                     runs)
#   version                        - show
#                                     gqlgen
#                                     version
#   completion <shell>             - generate
#                                     shell
#                                     completion
#                                     (bash +
#                                     zsh +
#                                     fish +
#                                     powershell)
#   help [command]                 - show
#                                     help
#                                     for
#                                     command
#
# `init` flags:
#       --config <file>            - config
#                                     file
#                                     path
#                                     (default
#                                     gqlgen
#                                     .yml)
#       --server <file>            - server
#                                     output
#                                     file
#                                     (default
#                                     server
#                                     .go)
#       --schema <file>            - schema
#                                     output
#                                     file
#                                     (default
#                                     graph/
#                                     schema
#                                     .graphqls)
#
# `generate` flags:
#       --config <file>            - config
#                                     file
#                                     path
#                                     (default
#                                     gqlgen
#                                     .yml)
#       --verbose                  - verbose
#                                     debug
#                                     output
#
# Example invocations:
#   # Initialize new GraphQL project
#   mkdir my-graphql-app && cd my-graphql-app
#   go mod init github.com/me/my-graphql-app
#   go get github.com/99designs/gqlgen
#   gqlgen init
#
#   # Generate code from current schema
#   gqlgen generate
#
#   # Or just `gqlgen` (default is
#   # generate)
#   gqlgen
#
#   # Custom config file
#   gqlgen --config=./config/gqlgen.yml \
#     generate
#
#   # Generate shell completions
#   gqlgen completion zsh > \
#     ~/.zinit/completions/_gqlgen
#
#   # Show version
#   gqlgen version
#
#   # Init with custom paths
#   gqlgen init \
#     --config=gqlgen.yml \
#     --server=server.go \
#     --schema=schema.graphqls
#
# Typical gqlgen workflow:
#   1. Define schema in schema.graphqls
#      (Apollo Federation v2 + types +
#      queries + mutations + subscriptions)
#   2. Configure gqlgen.yml (resolver
#      packages + struct tags + custom
#      directives + plugin config)
#   3. Run `gqlgen generate` to produce:
#       - generated.go (resolvers
#         interface)
#       - models_gen.go (DTO structs)
#   4. Implement resolver functions in
#      resolver.go (your business logic)
#   5. Wire HTTP server (net/http +
#      gqlgen.NewExecutableSchema)
#   6. Run + test
#
# Configuration file (gqlgen.yml):
#   ```yaml
#   schema:
#     - "graph/*.graphqls"
#
#   exec:
#     filename: graph/generated.go
#     package: graph
#
#   model:
#     filename: graph/model/models_gen.go
#     package: model
#
#   resolver:
#     layout: follow-schema
#     dir: graph
#     package: graph
#     filename_template: "{name}.resolvers.go"
#
#   autobind:
#     - "github.com/me/my-app/graph/model"
#
#   models:
#     ID:
#       model:
#         - github.com/99designs/gqlgen/graphql.ID
#         - github.com/99designs/gqlgen/graphql.Int
#         - github.com/99designs/gqlgen/graphql.Int64
#
#   # Federation v2 support
#   federation:
#     filename: graph/federation.go
#     package: graph
#     version: 2
#   ```
#
